BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:New Americas Cinema: When Everybody Swims
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260428T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260428T210000
UID:ai1ec-148914-95206@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Through the voices of Olympic athletes\, water safety experts\
 , and families who have experienced both triumph and loss\, When Everyone 
 Swims explores the essential role of swimming in our lives.About When Ever
 yone SwimsWhen Everyone Swimsis a compilation of inspirational and insight
 ful stories about how everyone deserves access to pools and safe places to
  swim. Through powerful\, personal narratives\, the film celebrates resili
 ence and highlights how water literacy can help individuals from all backg
 rounds build healthy\, life-affirming relationships with the water. [90 mi
 n\; documentary\; English]A Q&A with director Jerald Harkness\, Olympic me
 dalist Lilly King\, and production consultant Dr. Tiffany Monique Quash\, 
 moderated by Bill Ramos of the School of Public Health\, will follow the s
 creening.
LOCATION:IU Cinema\, 1213 E. 7th Street\, Bloomington (on the North end of
  the IU Auditorium)
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/new-americas-cinema-when-everybody-swims/?insta
 nce_id=95206
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
