BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Finn: A New Musical- At the PB&J Cafe
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260517T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260517T140000
UID:ai1ec-140265-90581@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Constellation Stage & Screen presents “Finn: A New Musical- 
 At the PB&J Cafe\,” on stage May 1-17 at the Waldron Auditorium.From the
  creator of Doc McStuffins and Vampirina\, Finn is a heartwarming musical 
 adventure about a young shark on the brink of growing up. As he prepares t
 o join the fearsome Shark Guard\, Finn can’t shake the feeling that he
 ’s different from the other sharks. Deep inside\, he discovers a colorfu
 l fish inside him—a part of himself that longs to sparkle\, sing\, and d
 ance. As Finn embarks on a journey of self-discovery\, friendship\, and ad
 venture\, he finds the courage to be himself! Fun for all ages!PB&J Cafe: 
 A Dinner Theater for Kids! At the PB&J Cafe\, young theatergoers will enjo
 y a meal during the performance and leave with autographs from their favor
 ite characters.
LOCATION:Waldron Arts Center (122 S Walnut St)
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/finn-a-new-musical-at-the-pbj-cafe-2/?instance_
 id=90581
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Finn: A New Musical–a sensory-friendly performance–At the PB&J
  Cafe
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260517T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260517T180000
UID:ai1ec-140529-90740@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:From the creator of Doc McStuffins and Vampirina\, Finn is a h
 eartwarming musical adventure about a young shark on the brink of growing 
 up. As he prepares to join the fearsome Shark Guard\, Finn can’t shake t
 he feeling that he’s different from the other sharks. Deep inside\, he d
 iscovers a colorful fish inside him—a part of himself that longs to spar
 kle\, sing\, and dance. As Finn embarks on a journey of self-discovery\, f
 riendship\, and adventure\, he finds the courage to be himself! Fun for al
 l ages!PB&J Cafe: A Dinner Theater for Kids! At the PB&J Cafe\, young thea
 tergoers will enjoy a meal during the performance and leave with autograph
 s from their favorite characters.
LOCATION:Waldron Arts Center. 122 S. Walnut Street\, Bloomington
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/finn-a-new-musical-a-sensory-friendly-performan
 ce-at-the-pbj-cafe/?instance_id=90740
